## Phase 6 — Bill Allocations (Open Bills + Persist + Reload)

### Goal

Implement bill details using composite backend APIs while keeping existing payment APIs untouched.

### Codex Prompt

Implement bill allocations support.

Backend:

- Add GraphQL query `openBillDocuments(ledgerId, docKinds, asOnDate, search)`
- Add query `voucherCompositeById(voucherId)`
- Add mutation `saveVoucherComposite(input)`
- Add table `accounts.voucher_bill_allocations` and wire create/update atomically
- Keep existing `createVoucher` / `updateVoucherEntry` untouched

Frontend:

- Add `VoucherBillDetails` section gated by profile feature flag
- On save, call `saveVoucherComposite` if bill allocations are present; otherwise use existing save path
- On edit, load composite data to populate allocations

Run:

- Frontend: `npm run lint && npm run build`
- Backend: `cd backend && npm run test`
- Migrations when applicable: `cd backend && npm run db:migrate:tenant` (or `db:migrate:tenant:ps`)

### Exit Criteria

- Allocations persist and reload correctly.
- Open bills show outstanding entries only.
- Payment module remains unaffected.

